added.title: Top of the Titans: Best Rivals
added.description: From Trigon to Terra to Darkseid, Robin counts down the worst of the worst: the greatest villains to ever challenge the Teen Titans!

added.title: Top of the Titans: Dance Party!
added.description: Come correct because it's a Titans Dance Battle! Birdarang reviews the greatest dance songs in Teen Titans Go! history.

added.title: Top of the Titans: Beast Boy & Cyborg Songs
added.description: Birdarang counts down the best musical moments from the raddest bros you know, Beast Boy and Cyborg. Waffles!

added.title: Top of the Titans: Best Love Songs
added.description: The Titans follow their heart with songs devoted to their greatest relationships: Beast Boy & Raven, Cyborg & Jinx and the Titans & Food.

added.title: Top of the Titans:  Raddest Songs
added.description: From "Booty Scooty" to "Sour Grapes" to "The Night Begins to Shine," Birdarang is here to count down the raddest music from Teen Titans Go!

added.title: The Sorcerer
added.description: Gumball refuses to accept he is the only kid at school that doesn't have special powers. He convinces Mrs. Jotunheim, Hector's mom, to take him on as his apprentice but she soon learns leaving Gumball unsupervised around magic is a big mistake.

added.title: The Wicked
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to find a single nice quality about their neighbor, Mrs Robinson.

added.title: The Vacation
added.description: The Wattersons set off on a relaxing vacation and end up running for their lives! The Wattersons are swapping scary stories on a family vacation, when their car breaks down in the middle of the desert. They are left with no alternative but to trust a complete stranger, whose appearance matches the scary guy in Mom's story. When the stranger brings them to a derelict gas station, just as he did in mom's made-up scary story, the Wattersons can no longer pretend the story isn't coming true . . .

added.title: The Castle
added.description: When Mom is away "anything goes" and Dad's lack of rules soon attracts unwelcome houseguests.

added.title: The Laziest
added.description: Gumball and Darwin challenge Dad to a "lazy-off."

added.title: That Will Be All
added.description: Steven and the Gems make a daring escape!

added.title: Super Watermelon Island
added.description: Steven finds out what happened to all those sentient watermelons he created.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Political Power
added.description: The Gems cause a power outage in Beach City, and Steven helps Mayor Dewey do damage control.

added.title: Full Disclosure
added.description: Steven tries to avoid Connie so he doesn't have to tell her about his most recent harrowing adventure.

added.title: Ugly Moons
added.description: Muscle Man vows to prank someone.

added.title: Dumptown USA
added.description: Benson is going to fire Mordecai if Rigby can't bring him back from a bizarre land of dudes also known as Dumptown USA.

added.title: Birthday Gift
added.description: Rigby always gives Mordecai the worst birthday gifts, but this year it's going to be different.

added.title: Mordecai and Rigby Down Under
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to catch a flight to the USA.

added.title: Tants
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get back a gift that Pops gave them.

added.title: Betty
added.description: In Wizard City, a magic spell backfires and turns Ice King back into Simon. Now with Finn, Jake and Marceline's help, Simon finds a way to bring his beloved Betty back. Finally reunited with the love of his life, everything is great! There's just one catch...without his magic crown, Simon will die.

added.title: Hug Wolf
added.description: After an encounter with a Hug Wolf, Finn goes through a Jekyll and Hyde-like transformation becoming a hug-wolf himself!

added.title: Ken 10
added.description: We're back in the future with Ben 10K, and this time he has a son, Ken. On Ken's tenth birthday, Ben gives him his very own Omnitrix. Ben must come to learn to trust Ken with the power of the Omnitrix. Along the way, Ken befriends a kid named Devlin. Devlin turns out to be Kevin 11's son and was merely using Ken so he could break his dad out of the Null Void. Ben 10K and Ken then team up to take down Kevin 11. As for Devlin, he comes to realize his dad is a jerk, and realizes the error of his ways. He's able to redeem himself, proving he's a good kid and joining forces with "Team Tennyson."

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: Worm Bin
added.description: After his mom gets a worm bin, Jeff deals with the gross reality that he has a tub of bugs living in his kitchen, and Clarence obsesses over feeding the worms.

added.title: Blurred
added.description: After his reckless actions cause the escape of a dangerous Sharkticon weapons engineer, Sideswipe goes out of his way to recapture the 'Con and prove his value to the Team in fear of getting replaced by a younger, and faster, newcomer -­‐‑Rescue Bot Blurr!

added.title: Bee Cool
added.description: Bee, trying to prove that he can be as cool as Sideswipe and his "intern" Blurr, struggles to lead the Autobots against two Stunticons who stole a trailer full of Cybertronian weapons.

added.title: Be Afraid of the Dark
added.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

added.title: Paper Pete
added.description: The pages of the books in the Ooo library turn to Finn & Jake for help before the evil Moldari destroy them.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: The Chamber of Frozen Blades
added.description: In Ninja-mode, Finn and Jake break into Ice King's palace to catch him red-handed.

added.title: Dr. Animo and the Mutant Ray
added.description: Dr. Animo has broken out of jail, and has been tracking down Ben, intent on revenge. At the same time, Ben's broken off a piece of the Omnitrix, and as a result, has turned into weird alien combinations, i.e. StinkArms.

added.title: Space Race
added.description: With Clarence distracted by the mysterious power of the moon, his class competes to build the highest-flying rocket. Will Sumo's homemade bucket of bolts beat Belson's store-bought rocket?

added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: Classic Rock
added.description: Batman thinks he's helping a homeless old man who is being mugged on the street only to discover that the man is a powerful wizard being chased by demons in disguise. It turns out the wizard is on a mission to save Shazam from the clutches of Black Adam.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: Follow that Space Cab!
added.description: While Superman escorts his prisoner Mr. Mind between planets, he is attacked by Lobo who wants to collect a reward on Mind. Temporarily powered-down, Superman seeks Space Cabbie's help to get away from Lobo.

added.title: Clarence's Millions
added.description: When Clarence realizes the classroom "buddy star" system is leaving some kids behind, he creates his own form of currency called "Clarence Dollars." The new reward system promptly turns the entire school upside down.

added.title: Nickname
added.description: When a kid wants a cool nickname, UG tells him he has to earn it in the most legendary way ever: yard work!

added.title: Driver's Test
added.description: When a girl has trouble passing her driving test, Uncle Grandpa shows up to help her.  But when they accidentally set a Crazy Baby loose in the city, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to stop it... by teaching the girl how to drive!

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Ate My Homework
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa shows up and mistakenly eats a kid's Egyptian diorama for school, he helps the kid bring an actual pyramid to class, but accidentally unleashes an evil mummy on the world.

added.title: Under a Red Sun
added.description: Steppenwolf "boom tubes" Superman to a planet with a red sun in order to make the Man of Steel powerless. Somehow Batman and Big Barda have to locate the planet before Superman is destroyed.

added.title: Felonious Prose
added.description: The Warrior mission of finding a lost contact lens gets seriously compromised from Vambre's obsession with the latest Veronica Victorious novel.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Bad Bad Cop
added.description: Vambre and Prohyas pretend to be cops in their attempts to shakedown a dangerous bunch of pirates to find a broccoli smuggler.

added.title: Treasure Map
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang don't have money to pay for their meal at a restaurant.  But when they discover a treasure map, it could be the answer to all their problems.  Too bad the treasure map is actually a restaurant activity placemat.

added.title: Locked Out
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets locked out of his RV and accidentally sets off the security system, it's up to him and his friends to disarm it before it destroys them.

added.title: Thick as Thieves
added.description: Phil the Pilferer robs Vambre and Prohyas of their very best Magiswords so he can snag the Sheepy Mantis, but the Warriors find out that no Magisword is lame as they manage to keep Phil from becoming Thief of the Year.

added.title: Hat Trick
added.description: When Felix Faust steals Zatanna's magical top hat, the Justice League must help retrieve it before the evil wizard can use it to create a magic portal, releasing the demon Ghast.

added.title: Dungeons and Dayjobs
added.description: A botched mission leaves the Warriors in debt, so they take day jobs at Slugburger and sling Slugburgers for Witchy Simone!

added.title: When Wedding Bells Thaw
added.description: Finn must help plan the Ice King's bachelor party.

added.title: Champions of Breakfast
added.description: An epic battle between Vambre and her Waffle Magisword and Prohyas' Pancake Magisword escalates to a war that can only end when Grup solicits his Cave Weirdo pals to be peacemakers.

added.title: Freezer Burn
added.description: Batman and Firestorm team up to fight their respective cold villains, Mr. Freeze and Killer Frost. Complications arise when Firestorm's infatuation for the wily Ms. Frost gets the best of him.

added.title: Evil's Encore
added.description: Dr. Animo reminisces about when he once took control of the Plumber's HQ in Mount Rushmore. (Flashback episode.)

added.title: O Mother, Where Art Thou?
added.description: Ma Vreedle threatens to blow up the sun if Ben and the Plumbers don't find her missing son!

added.title: Mud Is Thicker Than Water
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Cousin Lucy try to find out how Psyphon's thugs are getting Plumber technology.

added.title: A Fistful of Brains
added.description: Grandpa Max and Rook are looking all over the galaxy for Ben, who is trapped on Khyber's hidden personal hunting preserve.

added.title: An American Benwolf in London
added.description: Ben and Rook are called to London England to investigate the Forever Knights' latest activities.

added.title: Him Diddle Riddle
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls must solve a series of Him's riddles to keep the Professor from having to pay.

added.title: Save Mojo/Substitute Creature
added.description: Save Mojo: An animal activist group sets out to protect Mojo, ensuring that he can behave like the naturally evil monkey that he is./Substitute Creature: A substitute teacher comes to Pokey Oaks and the girls are sure that this creature teacher is up to no good.

added.title: Telephonies/Tough Love
added.description: Telephonies: The Gangreen Gang gets hold of the Powerpuff Girls' Hotline and makes crank calls sending the Powerpuff Girls on a wild goose chases all over town./Tough Love: Everyone in Townsville loves the Powerpuff Girls! But the citizens have a sudden change of heart when Him sends out an evil gas turning the entire town against their favorite superheroes.

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever/Just Desserts
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever: It's raining in Townsville and there is no crime or villainy afoot. So the girls must stay inside and come up with their very own Powerpuff adventure./Just Desserts: The Smith Family is back and they want revenge. Harold, Maryanne and the kids become a super villain team and make it their goal to destroy the perfect Powerpuff family.

added.title: Warts and All
added.description: Witchy Simone accidentally turns Vambre into a frog and Prohyas and Witchy try to change her back.

added.title: Too Commercial
added.description: The Warriors go advertising crazy; Grup tries to stop them for their own good!

added.title: Like Water for Bimm
added.description: Vambre helps to get Bimm over her mission crippling fear of water.

added.title: The Pecking Order
added.description: Professor Cyrus hires the Warriors to take Frank-Paul through a treacherous mountain pass so he can molt at the top of Mt. Chickicken.

added.title: Manlier Fish the Fishlier Man
added.description: With the help of a conch shell genie, Man Fish upgrades himself in various ways to defeat the Warriors.

added.title: The Lanolion Sleeps Tonight
added.description: Bimm and Familiar shadow the Warriors on a mission in the Sheepy Jungle, but put under such close scrutiny, the Warriors find that they're unable to be themselves!

added.title: The Ballad of Sailor Sidney
added.description: A Warrior mission to find missing Sailor Sidney for the Keelhaul Cove Pirates.

added.title: Extreme Dreams
added.description: Phibby Croax hires the Warriors for the MOST EXTREME EXPERIENCE EVER!

added.title: Forever a Fishstick
added.description: After a misfire with Fishstick Magisword, Prohyas copes with completing Warrior missions as a fish stick!

added.title: Sorry for Party OCHing
added.description: The Warriors struggle to keep poise at Princess Zange's exclusive party, but all bets are off when a feud with Witch Way escalates into a Magic vs. Magiswords war!

added.title: A Mind Is a Terrible Thing
added.description: The Warriors easily thwart Phil's latest plan with Legendary Knowledge Magisword so Phil repeatedly tries to steal it from them.

added.title: Bewitched, Bothered and Bothered Some More!
added.description: Flonk hires the Warriors to make Witch Way change his brother Helmut from a frog back to human.

added.title: Train on a Snake
added.description: Lady Hiss hires the Warriors to train her to be super tough.

added.title: King of the Zombeez
added.description: Frostferatu hires the Warriors to rid his castle of Zombeez when Neddy and a power mad zombie-bee queen take over.

added.title: Hiccup the Volume
added.description: Monkey Chunks has hiccups and Biblia Tick hires the Warriors to get rid of them.

added.title: Ghosthaste
added.description: Vambre becomes enamored of a poltergeist within Ghost Magisword and Prohyas must save her before his sister becomes a ghost herself!

added.title: Hangry Hangry Hoppus
added.description: The Warriors battle a monster version of Hoppus, the rabbit transformed by the Cursed Garlic Magisword.

added.title: Pachydermus Packard and the Camp of Fantasy
added.description: A doctor orders Mr. Pachydermus to have an adventure, so he attends the Warriors' super-annoying, "Fantasy Camp"!

added.title: Let's Team Up Because We Aren't Bad Friends
added.description: The Warriors fear that they've been ignoring their pals, so they team up with Witchy Simone and Noville for a BIG MISSION, only to discover that their friends aren't into it anymore.

added.title: Day of Fun-Ship
added.description: Starfire and Blackfire must protect the zoo from King Shark and realize they have more in common than they thought.

added.title: Fresh Ares Part 1
added.description: A peaced out Ares comes to Metropolis to see Wonder Woman, but his peaceful outlook is ruined when Catwoman steals the Amulet of Harmonia.

added.title: A Fury Scorned
added.description: Lashina breaks into Belle Reve and poisons Commissioner Gordon. Batgirl and Hawkgirl must find the antidote before it's too late.

added.title: It's a Superful Life
added.description: The girls want to make this an extra special holiday by brightening the lives of Metropolis citizens.

added.title: New Perry-Spective
added.description: Batgirl, Big Barda, and Lady Shiva set off in the Mobile HQ to wrangle Perry the Parademon. Perry playfully destroys various bits of Metropolis as the supers chase him. The supers manage to catch him and wait in anticipation, thinking Granny Goodness is behind this. However, it seems Perry has been abandoned by his previous owner, and just wants to play. Big Barda decides to keep Perry as her pet.

added.title: Jetsetters
added.description: Wonder Woman is teaching Frost how to fly the Invisible Jet when Killer Moth detects them and begins to attack. Frost takes the ejector Turbo Seat to fight back. However, the jet is damaged by Killer Moth's ship, and the jet begins to plummet. The ship goes into emergency lockdown and Wonder Woman is trapped. She manages to lift the jet from the inside and crash into the bay instead of the city. Frost makes a giant ice cube that allows the jet to float and freezes Killer Moth's plane. With Killer Moth defeated, Supergirl melts the ice around Wonder Woman's jet and Batgirl restores functionality to the jet's tech. Wonder Woman emerges unscathed.

added.title: Around Metropolis in 80 Seconds
added.description: Wonder Woman and Supergirl are facing off to see who's fastest, but when they keep tying, they decide to race sans superpowers. Harley hates to be left out and joins the race. As Wonder Woman and Supergirl zoom around Metropolis, they spot a bank robbery in progress and compete to see who can catch the criminals first. While they're distracted, Harley wins the race.

added.title: Stealth 101 Part 1
added.description: Batgirl and Ivy are partnered for Crazy Quilt's stealth suit design project.

added.title: Wildside Part 2
added.description: With Lion-Mane subdued, Batgirl, Starfire, and Beast Boy must find all the escaped zoo animals and return them to the zoo. With the help of zoo volunteer, Mari McCabe (Vixen), they return the animals to their proper place at the zoo.

added.title: For Art's Sake
added.description: It's the SHH Student Art Fundraiser and the Double Dare Twins have stolen a masterpiece from the show! It's up to Katana and Supergirl to stop them and recover the painting. But when Supergirl is knocked out by kryptonite and Katana's sword is stolen, Katana must improvise and use her art supplies to defeat the Double Dare Twins.

added.title: Spring Prison Break
added.description: Frost reads her "How I Spent Spring Break" essay and we flashback to the tale of how Katana and Frost formed the first "Task Force X" to stop Lashina from breaking the Female Furies out of Belle Reve. During the battle between the SHH Heroes and the Furies, Barda redeems herself and joins the side of the good guys.

added.title: Stealth 101 Part 2
added.description: Batgirl and Ivy learn to appreciate each other's style as they fight Killer Moth.

added.title: Fresh Ares Part 3
added.description: With Catwoman's help, the supers return the amulet to Ares and save the day.

added.title: Body Electric
added.description: Giganta causes an electric blackout and Batgirl enlists the help of Thunder and Lightning,

added.title: Batnapped
added.description: Batgirl is kidnapped by Killer Moth, who wants to make her his partner! Too bad Batgirl already has a partner, Supergirl.

added.title: Tales from the Kryptomites Part 1
added.description: Lena Luthor uses kryptonite remnants from Supergirl's ship to create living Kryptomites.

added.title: Seeing Red
added.description: A red Kryptomite, loose at Super Hero High, brings out everyone's mean side.

added.title: Wildside Part 1
added.description: Batgirl, Beast Boy and Starfire are picnicking in the park when Lion-Mane's menagerie of entranced animals attack the park. The heroes must save the citizens and stop Lion-Mane.

added.title: Ares up There
added.description: When Wonder Woman is home for a holiday, Ares, the god of war, attacks.

added.title: Techless Tuesday
added.description: Mrs. Clayface steals all of Batgirl's gadgets in an effort to break her husband out of Arkham.

added.title: Fresh Ares Part 2
added.description: As Ares reigns destruction on Metropolis, the supers must recover the amulet.

added.title: Fight Flub
added.description: Katana and Big Barda try to prove their own fighting style is the best when the Double Dare Twins attack.

added.title: Gorilla Warfare
added.description: The supers must save Gorilla Grodd when his former army comes to "rescue" him from SHH.

added.title: Surprise
added.description: Harley enlists the help of Katana and Bumblebee in hiding a surprise birthday present for Batgirl in her dorm room. But when they sneak into Batgirl's dorm, they are accosted by Batgirl's booby traps.

added.title: Dog Day After School
added.description: A Krytptonian is loose in Metropolis! After following the wake of school destruction, Supergirl is reunited with Krypto the Super Dog.

added.title: Tales from the Kryptomites Part 2
added.description: The supers must save Metropoils from the army of Kryptomites.

added.title: New Beginnings
added.description: Wonder Woman shows Supergirl around Super Hero High.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Supergirl
added.description: Supergirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Batgirl vs. Supergirl
added.description: Batgirl and Supergirl face off in a quest for the last piece of superfood cake.

added.title: Quintessential Harley
added.description: When Harley's web videos go viral, she deals with the unexpected consequences of fame.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Harley Quinn
added.description: Harley Quinn is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: License to Fly
added.description: Batgirl builds her Batjet. But before she can fly, she must pass the Flyer's Exam.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Batgirl
added.description: Batgirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Doubles Trouble
added.description: Katana chooses Supergirl as her tennis doubles partner, but Supergirl's powers are too much for the game.

added.title: Franken-Ivy
added.description: Ivy creates a new plant pet which grows out-of-control and attacks Metropolis.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Katana
added.description: Katana is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: The Blunder Games
added.description: As part of the Advanced Survival Skills class, Batgirl is dropped off in a remote island and must make it to the designated meeting spot before sunset. But when her equipment malfunctions, Batgirl must rely on a different set of super skills.

added.title: The Cheetah Who Cried Wolf
added.description: Cheetah attempts to win Hero of the Month through various Save the Day situations.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Frost
added.description: Frost is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Dude, Where's My Invisible Jet?
added.description: Wonder Woman loses her invisible jet.

added.title: Hawkgirl's Day Off
added.description: Hawkgirl's friends surprise her with a relaxing day at the spa. But when Hawkgirl takes on Mrs. Clayface in the mud bath, her friends find that fighting crime is Hawkgirl's preferred way of relaxing.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Hawkgirl
added.description: Hawkgirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: The Ultimate Accessory
added.description: Bumblebee must design an accessory for her Weaponomics class. But instead of designing for herself, she finds more inspiration in her friends.

added.title: Ring of Mire
added.description: Star Sapphire loses her violet lantern ring down the drain and must venture into the sewers. Ew ew ew!

added.title: Hero of the Month: Star Sapphire
added.description: Star Sapphire is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Riddle of the Heart
added.description: The Riddler stages a series of crimes in order to lure Batgirl to the rose garden where he asks her to the dance.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Cyborg and Starfire
added.description: Cyborg and Starfire are both anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Roomies Return: Frost's Bite
added.description: When Frost can't get her warmth from any of her normal sources, her grumpiness causes icy havoc around the school.

added.title: The Odd Couple
added.description: Harley and Lady Shiva are paired for a stake out assignment and must capture a villainous named Cheshire.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Lady Shiva
added.description: Lady Shiva is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Cold Blooded
added.description: Frost catches a cold and each sneeze and sniffle causes her to freeze everything around her.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Beast Boy
added.description: Beast Boy is anointed Hero of the Month.

added.title: Welcome to Super Hero High
added.description: The school's official greeting video hosted by Principal Waller. Principal Waller introduces the school and curriculum to potential new students.

added.title: All About Super Hero High
added.description: Wonder Woman arrives at Super Hero High. Waller introduces Bumblebee as the Ambassador to New Students. Bumblebee gives Wonder Woman the tour of Super Hero High and introduces her to some of the main Supers.

added.title: Roomies
added.description: Wonder Woman meets her new dorm-mate, Harley Quinn. Harley is obsessed with the new girl, but Wonder Woman just wants some peace and quiet so she can study. In the end, Wonder Woman and Harley hit off their unexpected friendship.

added.title: Power Outage
added.description: It's Wonder Woman's first day of Flyer's Ed and her chance to prove to Red Tornado, the instructor, what a great flyer she is. But her lap through the aerial obstacle course is fraught with disaster when Cheetah takes control of Wonder Woman's flight safety belt.

added.title: Crazy Quiltin
added.description: Wonder Woman is introduced to an important rite-of-passage for all new students at the school: creating your own iconic super hero suit. But super suit design is not Wonder Woman's forte. She brings in Katana, Bumblebee, and Harley to help her in this important task, but the results leave something to be desired.

added.title: Fall into Super Hero High
added.description: Harley Quinn reveals she made a tribute video for her friends, which they learn is a montage of them screwing up while using their powers. Their embarrassment is heightened when they learn Harley has accidentally uploaded the video and it's gone viral! Seeing the absurdity and laughing at herself, Wonder Woman breaks the girls' stunned, mortified silence. The laugh catches on. Because of Wonder Woman's leadership, all the girls who were initially embarrassed are able to laugh at themselves.

added.title: Designing Disaster
added.description: Wonder Woman finishes her super suit for Crazy Quilt's class and it's time to try it out. But the suit is a mish-mash of super hero tropes and isn't practical for saving the day. Her attempts to respond to a Save the Day drill end in disaster as her suit trips her up.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Bumblebee
added.description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M. is Bumblebee. Waller shows a video montage of Bumblebee's exploits including saving her friends plus little comedic beats where Bumblebee changing size causes her to split a seam in her costume.

added.title: Clubbing
added.description: Principal Waller tells Poison Ivy that she needs to join a club in order to fulfill her extracurricular requirements. However, clubs are not introverted Ivy's idea of fun. Hawkgirl and Bumblebee invite Ivy to join the Junior Detective Society. Miss Martian and Starfire give Ivy the pitch for the Model United Planets. Katana and Beast Boy want her for Band Club. But then, the glimmering test tubes of Science Club catch Ivy's eye. Ivy adds her name to the sign-up sheet manned by Frost and Flash. Later, during the first Science Club meeting, Ivy shows off her modified plants, which creates chaos for Star Sapphire. Ivy grins. Clubs are fun!

added.title: Weaponomics
added.description: It's demonstration day in Lucius Fox's Weaponomics class. Catwoman wields her whip. Hawkgirl swings her mace. But when Wonder Woman demonstrates her lasso, a sneaky maneuver from Cheetah causes her to lasso Mr. Fox, who spills his secrets in the lasso's grip. The incident leads to Wonder Woman getting detention!

added.title: Hero of the Month: Poison Ivy
added.description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M. is Poison Ivy. Waller shows a video montage of Poison Ivy's exploits as Ivy saves the students from the grip of her out-of-control plants.

added.title: Saving the Day
added.description: It's time for Wonder Woman to reveal her new super suit for Crazy Quilt's final grade. Bumblebee, Harley and Ivy watch from the sidelines in support of their friend. Wonder Woman steps onto the catwalk and reveals her new outfit. But before Crazy Quilt announces Wonder Woman's grade, the Save the Day alarm buzzes! Wearing her new costume, Wonder Woman leads Bumble Bee, Harley, and Ivy on a mission to save the day! They must save Mr. Fox who's stuck on top of the Amethyst! The girls save their teacher, but in the process, Wonder Woman discovers that Cheetah was behind this malicious deed. In the grip of Wonder Woman's lasso, Cheetah confesses all her crimes.

added.title: Hero of the Month: Wonder Woman
added.description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M is Wonder Woman. Waller shows a video montage of Wonder Woman's exploits, which is mix of big heroic moments, and the small beats of friendship, laughter and fun.
